comments.comment_text:
Other then the places suggested by Valentina Saltarelli:
-Palazzo Barberini (here you can see a masterpiece of Raffaello, La Fornarina);
-Palazzo Doria Pamphijli;
-Ara Pacis;
-Parco dell'Appia Antica (where Via Appia started);
-Terme di Caracalla (magnificent scenario fo opera too) ;
-Palazzo Farnese;;
-San Pietro in vincoli (here you ca see the Mosè by Michelangelo, famous because after the realization the author was able to rotate the head of 25°);
-San Giovanni Basilica;
-If you want to see some Caravaggio masterpiece without tickets go to San Luigi dei Francesi Church, Sant'Agostino Basilica, Santa Maria del Popolo Basilica.
These are only some suggestions of what I'm remembering in this time, but there are many other.
